The paper proposes an algorithm for reinforcement learning, which is a subfield of machine learning. The use of upper confidence bounds and state aggregation suggests that the paper may belong to the sub-category of machine learning (cs.LG). Additionally, the paper deals with continuous state space, which suggests that it may also belong to the sub-category of artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The use of optimization techniques and the focus on control suggest that the paper may also belong to the sub-category of control systems (cs.SY). The paper also deals with data structures and algorithms, which suggests that it may belong to the sub-category of data structures (cs.DS). Finally, the paper deals with multi-agent systems, which suggests that it may also belong to the sub-category of multi-agent systems (cs.MA).
